<p>Associates working in special noxious, dangerous environment, doing special heavy works will have 04 more annual leave days per year under such standards as prescribed by Ministry of Sciences and Technologies and Ministry of Public Health.</p>
<p><strong>Pro-ration of Annual Leave</strong></p>
<p>In the event an associate join/resign on or before the 15<sup>th</sup> of the month, annual leave entitlement shall be calculated on a pro-rated basis.</p>
<p><strong>Annual Leave during Probation Period</strong></p>
<p>No Associate under probation will be eligible to apply AL. Upon successful completion of the stipulated probationary period, Associate will be eligible to apply AL. Advanced AL application is not allowed.</p>

<p>Carry Forward Annual Leave</p>
<p>Annual leave entitlement for the current year may be accumulated and carried forward to the following year <br /> not later than 30 June. Annual leave not taken thereafter shall be forfeited and no compensation shall be</p>
<p>considered.</p>
<p>Any exception to the above clause shall be approved on a case to case basis by the management (GM/PM, HOD and H RM)</p>
<p>Encashment of Annual Leave</p>
<p>Annual Leave Balance by last working day for resigned associate (voluntary and/or involuntary) will be encashed and paid to the Associate together with his/her final payment.</p>
<p>Subject to mutual agreement between the HOD and the Associate, annual leave can be used to offset the notice period.</p>
<p>Special Case</p>
<p>Any Associate who has to work during his/her registered annual leave schedule due to job demand with the approval of his/her superior shall be entitled to receiving a further payment of 200% his/her daily basic pay for each and every working day during such an annual leave schedule.</p>
<p>An alternate option to compensate the annual leave can be considered upon agreement from all HODS and Associate.</p>
